	Best hotel in Vegas!	Well I'd like to start off by thinking the staff for the early check in. I must say a complementary upgraded room would have been nice. However, their normal rooms are just fine. We had great service throughout are stay. From the valet, to the bellhop, and to the servers at the Coranado Cafe, everything was great. We always stay here when were in Vegas. While it is 10 minutes from the strip, everything you need is here. The strip is just a mess with the terrible traffic. I even saw Floyd Mayweather while playing some blackjack in their great casino. We hope to be coming back in December. They could however drop the need to charge $15 a night to use internet.	
	Just what the doctor ordered.	First of all, it always confuses me when people downgrade a property for something they could have easily researched. The South Point is frequently criticized for being so far from the Strip. I think that was the point, and as far as I'm concerned it's a strength, not a weakness. During my latest trip I took an early morning drive down the Strip. No thank you. For my taste, SP is both a perfect size and distance from the action. With a rental nothing is more than 10-15 minutes away anyway.I also would prefer there were no charges for the Internet and exercise room, but the fact is that is the norm in LV. I don't know of any property that offers complimentary Internet and gym access. Criticizing the SP for something everyone else does doesn't make sense to me.So we what it doesn't have, how about what it can offer. For my money, what little of it I need to spend to stay at SP, there is no better property in all of Vegas. During a recent stay I paid all of $100 for a 3- night stay. For that very reasonable price I got to stay in a large, clean room that would put to shame many room from higher-end hotels. The casino is a perfect size as well. Big enough to offer a variety of games, but not so large it had different zip codes.During my visit I had two fantastic meals - one at Primarily Prime Rib and the other at Silverado (there pretzel bread is the absolute best). Having stayed at SP before, but not having tried the buffet, I also decided to give it a whirl. It was satisfactory. I have nothing to either overly complain or compliment.In leading up to my recent trip I had a hard time deciding where to stay. I'm happy I chose the SP, and would happily do so again. Very happily.	
