Nov 19 2009 	You take the good you take the bad you take them both and there you have	This is an interesting property to review. The real estate is very nice. The rooms are large and comfortable. The housekeeping staff does an excellent job. The restaurants are nice. The food is good and the prices are very reasonable. I have been to many hotels that are not remotely as nice as this one. If you are looking for a place to gamble, sleep and eat this is a great choice. Overall the employees are well trained. I'm guessing that this resort has a very well thought out training curriculum that is focused on roles and responsibilities. The training could be improved by focusing more on customer satisfaction. I felt like I had my role and the employees had theirs and that rules were rules.  If you want to have a drink at South Point you have two alternatives. You can sit on the casino floor which I do not find relaxing or you can go upstairs and listen to a bunch of televisions in the Mexican bar. I recognize that the owner of South Point is not pursuing the Hip Hop demographic but a simple club would help. If that is not possible it would be a significant selling point if the resort provided a shuttle to the strip. Even if there was a charge for a 24 hour pass to go back and forth it would be preferable to being completely isolated and dependent upon taxi cabs. It will cost you $25 plus tip each way if you want to go &quot;down town&quot;. Sixty dollars to go dancing or to the mall is outrageous and will keep me from staying at South Point in the future. This place has great potential. I think with some small tweaks it could be GREAT.	
