Sep 30 2009 	Comfortable stay off strip good price	Comfortable Hotel off the strip. As others have mentioned, you will need a car. It's a $30 cab fare (as told from another guest who took a cab) each way to the strip.. there are no shuttles to the strip or any attractions. There is a free shuttle from the airport, however the shuttles don't start till 6:00am and we had to be to the airport before then, so that was inconvenient. Rooms are very large, thought the beds were very comfortable, the sheets were even soft &amp; Pillows were OK too. Good nights rest. We were at the very end of a hall which is nice cuz we had no traffic by our room so it was quiet. Pool was OK, it gets full of splashing kids on the weekends which was a bit annoying to me, as I was trying to relax. Weekdays the pool was nice though &amp; not crowded.  The Garden Buffet was a great deal...coupon when you check in for 2 for 1 price on weekdays...and it was only $6.95 to begin with. The Buffet goes up to $13.95 on Sat/Sun. We thought the buffet was very good.. it had a very large selection of many different items.. honestly if you can't find something on there you like, maybe you are just to fussy. We thought it was very good. The Deli is a bit over priced, but it is Vegas. Movie Theater was good. Love the Happy Hour Marguarita special at Miguels Tequila Bar from 5-7 pm.. $2 marguaritas... can't beat it!! Wanted to try the other restaurants but never got around to it.The only problem we had is that at times our keys wouldn't work... We had 2 keys so usually one key would work, but not very convenient when you aren't together all the time.On several occasions one of us couldn't get in, because the key wouldnt work, so we had to call &amp; wait for someone to come up to let us in.. or run all the way down to the desk &amp; get a replacement. very annoying &amp; inconvenient.All in all a good stay.. very reasonably priced.	
