mically distressed times, the South Point was doing a brisk business. I think this is because they provide excellent accomodations, friendly cheerfull staff and a variety of things to do and places to eat all at a VERY affordable price. The casino looked very nice and was quite busy. But we are not gamblers, as it seems to me that 95% of the money people gamble goes to the casino, and I can't afford to take that kind of risk. But if you like to gamble, South Point has all the gambling options of any major, established casino in Vegas. There were quite a few Penny slots, so if you find slot machines entertaining, you could entertain yourself for quite some time without losing too much money. The hotel also has an on site movie theatre with about 8 movies showing, and a bowling alley. They give you coupons for disounts at these also. And they have a beautiful pool area. All in all, highly recommended.	
