Jan 13 2009 	Good locals casino (far from main strip)	I am a gambler, so casinos will often &quot;comp&quot; my rooms and meals. &quot;Comp&quot; means complimentary, free. This trip was my first visit to South Point, and the hotel room was free before I arrived. So I can't comment on the room rates.Location (poor). This is a locals hotel and casino. Yes, it is on the strip, but many miles south of Madalay Bay and the rest of the strip hotels and casinos. If you are planning to visit the &quot;real&quot; strip or downtown you will need a rental car. The good news is that cheap rental cars are easy to get in LV. The hotel is supposed to have a shuttle, but I didn't try it. I just rented a cheap car.Room (very good). Enough room and nicely appointed. I don't spend much time in my room (other than shower and sleep) when in LV. Maid service did a good job and everything appeared to be in working order. One very big negative is the internet (see below). Temperature controls were quiet. That's a big plus for me since I'm a light sleeper.Internet access (very bad). Like a lot of hotels SP is trying to grossly overcharge customers for internet access. Only the hotel's hotspots can be found on this property. Some center strip hotels you can access hotspots outside your hotel, but not at SP. Both the wifi and wired connections are unbelievably expensive. Stay away from it. I'd drive down the street to a Starbucks or McDonalds and use their wifi service instead.Gambling (good). I didn't see anything to call overwhelmingly great or terrible. Note, many LV casinos have significantly worsened their rules in recent years. In fact, LV is no longer my favorite destination for solely gambling purposes because so many places have worsened their rules. SP is ok. SP's cage and club are much too slow. I saw 2 hour lines that the player's club.Food (fair). Quality was good in the buffet and ok in the cafe. Prices were too high in my opinion. My meals were paid for, but I don't know if I'd go there without the comps.Atmosphere (cowboy). You'll swear your in the old west. A high percentage of the patrons walk around with cowboy hats, fig leaf sized belt buckles, boots and jeans. If you like red necks and cowboys, you'll love it. Note, they have many rodeo and similarly related events in the arena here.Family (fair). I don't like kids in a casino. Like too many LV locations you can't get anyplace without going through the middle of the casino floor: front desk, parking garage, room access, restaurants, everything goes through the casino. After going through the casino floor you can access the arena, movie theaters, bowling lanes. There are things for families to do here. But I don't like that the kids and strollers have to go through the middle of the casino all the time.Smoke (bad). Like a lot of casinos the smoke handling is rather poor. I'm surprised because a newer location like SP should have built in better smoke handling. On a Saturday night, it's bad.Parking (good). Easy access to LV Blvd (many miles south of the real strip), to I-15. Quick and easy getting to and from the airport. Much easier than center strip locations. Valet was reasonably quick, and Summarybest: roomsworst: smoke handling	
