Nov 24 2008 	Good with Some Issues	We stayed at South Point Hotel in September 2008. Our visit was nice and comfortable but there were some issues with the hotel, mainly with customer service.Hotel: The hotel is family friendly and nice looking, but don’t expect the extravagant look of other Vegas hotels. It is new and absolutely okay-looking, but the décor is plain. The reason we chose it was the children’s entertainment. They have a movie theatre, bowling and arcade. The arcade was lots of fun for the kids, but we never got to bowl – the wait on a Saturday night was about 90 minutes. The casino, pool and gift shop were good.Rooms: The rooms were clean and comfortable, and to our surprise, very spacious. That was good because the kids didn’t feel too crowded. I agree with another reviewer – the towels were too small/thin, but the sheets were especially soft and luxurious. However, the furniture and décor were very plain and simple. We didn’t care because we traveled with friends and were more interested in the company than in a fancy look.Restaurants: The first night we ate at Coronado Café. It was a disaster. Out of 11 entrees, only one was edible. Most of us didn’t touch the food, which was cold and tasteless. The dishes didn’t arrive together, the service was extremely slow and sloppy, and the waiters hardly understood English. They even forgot some of the items we ordered, which wasn’t a big loss anyway. Prices were cheap, but what good is it if you can’t eat your food? Don’t waste your time there. In the morning we ate at Garden Buffet. That was a much better experience than the night before. For breakfast, it’s completely okay, and not expensive. The selection was rich and food was good+. They have different sections (Mexican, Italian, American, Asian, etc.), and everybody can find something to eat - absolutely recommended for breakfast. Service was better than at the café. Then at night we ate at Primarily Prime Rib. It was nice. The only problem was that they couldn’t accommodate such large group as ours (24 people), so we had to sit in two separate tables, but it was worth it. Although we experienced better food at other fine dining restaurants, this one had absolutely great food for the prices. The portions were big and the wine was good, the selection was average, and the food was good++, but not extraordinary or unique. However, no one was disappointed. The service was wonderful and extra quick, and the waiters were super nice. When my husband asked for jalapeno, which they didn’t have, they ran to the restaurant next door to get him some. If you don’t want to leave the hotel or spend big bucks at the other hotels, Prime Rib is totally acceptable for a nice dinner. Customer service:This is where the hotel needs the most improvement. Because of the size of our party, we had to make multiple phone calls/reservations. Every representative gave us different information about everything, and some were very unprofessional on the phone. They made an error and gave someone in our group the key to someone else’s room. That was outrageous. Luckily, it was people who knew each other, but I’ve never heard of an error like this – a stranger getting the key to your room! When the guests who originally had the room tried to get in, their key was deactivated so they were locked out. It took the front desk a long time to figure out the error and fix it, and they barely apologized for the mistake. We had to go to higher management for that. They should really train their staff better. To summarize, the hotel is nice and we recommend it, especially if you travel with kids, but keep your expectations on the low side and avoid Coronado Café. For the hotel's low rates - it's worth it.	
Nov 20 2008	Would love to return to the South Point	I stayed at the South Point from Oct 5 through 9, 2008. Could not believe how large the room was for the price paid. Watch for Internet special rates even after you book. As long as you booked online through the hotel's site, they'll honor any special offers that are posted for your time frame. The buffet was wonderful for both breakfast and dinner, especially with the coupon for a free bottle of wine (full size). I booked a facial at the spa with another friend and we spent hours there just enjoying the pools and showers after we were done. The staff at the spa in particular were extremely helpful whenever we asked for something extra. We had a group of 20 for dinner at Don Vito's restaurant. We weren't happy with the seating arrangement and the hostess totally redid a section of the restaurant so that we could all sit together. The food there was first rate. I used the shuttle to go to the airport on departure - left on time and smooth ride to the airport. The only drawback for some might be the distance from the strip - I'd say 15 minutes by car - but I've stayed on the strip before and didn't feel the need to be so close this time. We went up two nights to the strip, once by private bus for our group of 20, another night by cab. Overall, I couldn't have been more pleased.	
