ed in the reviews about the Shuttle service. We reserved the &quot;Airport&quot; shuttle 24 hours in advance for our pick-up. No problems. The same again for the return to the airport. This shuttle drops/pick-up in the main entrance to the hotel.The &quot;Mandalay Bay&quot; shuttle runs approximately on the hour from South Point. This shuttle leaves from the north side of the casino. Depending on traffic, it was no real problem. (note: according to the Mandalay Bay shuttle driver, this service will end December 14th.)We feel that the hotel should keep it, as its a nice selling point to be able to hop aboard and then catch the tram to the Excalibur. There are taxis, but they are gonna cost you about $45 return.2. Smokey Casino. Much more than the casino at the Mandalay Bay. We attributed this to the casino being packed both Saturday and Sunday night. Maybe their system cannot keep up, but if you are a non-smoker you will notice.3.Internet is not free. It will cost you approx $12 for 24 hours, but we looked around at a couple of other hotels and this seems to be the norm. Again it would be a nice selling point, if they didn't charge or gave you an hour free a day, or something like that.Overall we had a good time. We both agreed that the staff at this hotel was one of the more accomodating and friendly that we have dealt with in sometime. Another trip down the pipe...Later from Ladner	
