Oct 4 2008 	Great Value for the Money	Just got back from 3 nights at the South Point Hotel. Found a great rate of $57/night on Expedia. Even though this property is not around the &quot;big hotels&quot; of the Strip, the rooms and services offered were equal if not better than some that are on The Strip. Parking is plentiful and easy to get to hotel from the parking lot. Check in is quick &amp; efficient --- all arrangements were in order. My room on the 9th floor did not have a great view, but otherwise it was great. Very roomy, clean, large flat screen, clean comfortable bed; free in- room safe; separate vanity area from the bath/toilet; room service. Definitely use the coupon book that is provided when you check in. It can really save you a few bucks! And make sure you sign up for their Slot Club card, &quot;The Club&quot;. You rack up points quickly and can cash it out for $$$. There's a good variety of sit down restaurants plus a quick service deli that has outrageous sandwiches and desserts. The ice cream parlor and Seattle's Best Coffee is a great pick me up too. It's a bit on the smoky side, so if you're sensitive to smoke, then this may be a concern. But otherwise this is a great property and I would definitely recommend it and stay again the next time I&quot;m in Vegas. I don't have any negative things to say about the shuttle service to Mandalay Bay. The longest I had to wait was 15-20 minutes. But it's worth it since if I were to take a cab, it would cost approx. $20 + tip (one way).	
Oct 4 2008	Great Place Off The Strip	Just came back from a 4 night enjoyable stay at the South Point.Airport shuttle picked me up at quarter after the hour (I think) at Bus Bay #17 on Lower Level.Check in was reasonably quick and front desk staff courteous.Room was spacious and comfortable. Big 42&quot; plasma TV a bonus for those who need to watch television while on holidays.Large pool in back. Great for swimming, not so great for quiet time as they seem to want to continuously play loud music all day.Large bowling alley (something like 64 lanes), great for kids.Multiplex theater, great for kids.Casino...REALLY SMOKEY!!!...not so great for kids or adults.Buffet...reasonably priced...good food. (If you want a truly great buffet experience, try the Spice Market Buffet at Planet Hollywood. You can get a $5 off coupon there just by registering in their casino for a player's club card).Shuttle to the Mandalay Bay is great. Runs very frequently until 1:00 in the a.m. Off the shuttle, up the escalator, through the hotel, up the escalator and your at the Tram to Excalibur. There are 2 trams. The inside one stops at the Luxor before heading on to Excalibur, while the outside one goes direct. Once outside off of the tram, you are a short walk to New York, New York, MGM Grand, and a few blocks away from Planet Hollywood, Paris, Ballys, Bellagio and Caesars.For an adventure, hop on the Deuce (double decker bus) on the strip, and take it up to the Fremont area. You won't be disappointed (make sure you hang around in the evening for the Fremont street experience). The Deuce bus ride is $2 one way or $5 for an all day pass. It's a great A/C ride that'll give you a bit of a tour up the strip. Go upstairs on the bus...better view...less people.	
