d time about handing out some beads- then and only then- was I given some beads. Granted this seems like a stupid and petty complaint but it all adds to the fun &amp; atmosphere of the casino. Didn't eat at any of the resturants so I can't comment on them. The Seattle Coffee Company was wonderful in the morning and the people working there were always happy with smiles on their faces. A real treat when trying to face the morning- kudos to the Seattle Coffee Company baristas!Pool area was small but pleasant. The astroturf was hotter than the concrete so don't fool yourself thinking you can walk on the fake grass without sandles! I can only imagine how crowded it was during the summer and with the 800 hotel rooms being added that is only going to add to the crowding at the pool.Overall I have to say the hotel &amp; casino was very pleasant but without a rental car (which I did have) it would have been a real pain to wait on and take shuttles to and from the Strip and a real expense to take taxis. I'd definately stay here again IF there was no other option or if finances were tight but I'm a &quot;Strip&quot; kinda girl and would much rather be closer to the glitz and lights! I'd still recommend the South Point, can't go wrong if you get a nice low rate like I did.	
