Sep 25 2008 	Great rooms… but beware of the extras!	We spend 2 nights at the South Point in September 2008. Let’s start with the good stuff. The rate was about $75, which was quite a bit lower than the major hotels on the Strip (for the days we were there). The room that we had was very spacious and very modern. The AC worked well and was very quiet. The bathroom had a separate section for the toilet and shower and the room had a full size couch next to the king-sized bed. Another great thing that you will not find in the mega-hotels on the Strip is that you can park your car right in front of the main entrance. (There is also a parking garage but we never had to go there.)With respect to the location, the South Point advertises that they are 7 minutes from the Strip…. You will need in fact about 10 minutes to get to the Welcome to Fabulous Las Vegas sign at the beginning of the Strip but you must then budget another 10-15 minutes minimum to get your car parked in any one of the major mega-complex of the Strip. One way to shorten this a bit is take the truck road right after the Welcome to Fabulous Las Vegas sign. You will avoid all the traffic lights of the Strip. The South Point offers a shuttle to the Mandalay Bay resort but, again, this is the very first complex of the Strip and there will be a lot of walking to do if you intend to visit the other complexes further north.The disappointing points were as follows. On a nice Sunday afternoon with 108 degrees outside, the pool was closed for some “special event”….we were glad we were not traveling with kids… Also, beware of the extras. The WI-FI is $12.00 per day and the gym (which seemed quite nice) is a whoppy $15 per day (based on another experience, this is not uncommon in Las Vegas…)Finally, we had a booklet in the rooms with a set of coupons. The booklet included a 2 for 1 coupon for the breakfast buffet, which is pretty good (but definitely not as good as the buffets on the major hotels on the strip). Nevertheless, we had breakfast for 2 for a total of $6.95 + tx so it is difficult to complain.	
