Aug 10 2008	A very nice stay	We just returned from our trip to Las Vegas. This was our first visit to Vegas and we enjoyed our stay at South Point. We pick this hotel because of it being off the strip and the price was unbelievable. They have a special summer rate and our average price was around $57 per night. For what you get that was a terrific value, but do not be fooled. Some of the amenities that normally are free are fee based at this hotel. Those amenities are not deal breakers though. For example the gym and internet are fee based. I normally skip workouts on vacation, but I did miss the internet a little. This place is massive with more amenities than the average hotel. My nine year old compared it to a mall and I agree. We were lucky to be the first to stay in a new wing that just opened two days before we arrived. The room was brand new. The rooms are very large with Thomasville furnishings and granite counter tops in the bathrooms. The room also has a 42” LCD TV. The beds were a little too soft. The room being new had a minor problem. One of the walls did not have power and the engineers could not find the breaker when the outage was reported. The hotel immediately offered to send their staff to move us, but it was not a big deal to us. They fixed the problem the following day while we were out. The entire hotel also had a water outage that day, which was a big deal because it wasted some of our day, but that was fixed as well. Overall this is a good hotel compared to others on the strip which are in need of renovations. If we did not have the outages I would have easily given this hotel an excellent on our stay. If you are going soon try to catch the summer rates they can not be beat.	
