Jul 31 2008 	Nice surprise	We just needed a place to crash for a night and the day of our red-eye flight. I didn't want to pay an arm and leg, so I Priceline-ed this hotel for 45 bucks. I must say, I was pleasantly surprised. This hotel is waaaaaay off the strip, but tries to make up for that by having everything right there inside the hotel. We parked ourselves in the garage, and check-in was easy (although, hard to find, as in Las Vegas every hotel makes you walk through the entire casino before checking in or going to the garage). I asked for a room on a high floor away from the elevators, and we had a really quiet room on the 24th floor. This hotel is newish (2005) so everything is still fairly clean and modern. The room was surprisingly big. Two comfie queen beds, a sitting area, huge windows overlooking vegas, and a huge bathroom and separate toilet/shower area. Even the coffee maker was modern. There was extra room for us to open all of our luggage on the floor. Really nice, large flat screen tv. Bath &amp; bodyworks lotion/shampoo (Coconut Lime Verbena--our favorite) was a nice touch.The casino takes up most of the first floor, amongst some restaurants and bars. The food was so-so, but we expected that. When we checked in we were given a coupon booklet--lots of free stuff, so we ate at the breakfast buffet, two of us, for 6 bucks. Has a huge movie theater (16 screens?) and nice bowling alley. Lots of stuff for the kids to do while mommy goes and gambles for a couple of hours. The pool area was big, full of kids and semi-drunk adults. Pool water looked filmy and cloudy, so, I didn't swim too long. They have shuttles if you want to go to the strip, but we didn't venture, as we were there just long enough to eat, sleep, watch a movie, etc.Overall, this was a great value. It's a good place for a family to stay for a couple of days, or for those with time to spend at the hotel and venture to the strip (it's probably a good 3 miles).	
Jul 31 2008 	Great stay great value at The South Point	Wife and I stayed at The South Point for two nights, starting on July 27. It was great. We were on the 21st floor, room 2154. It was the perfect place to celebrate my wife's birthday!Security was at the elevators every evening and checked room keys. There was lots of security in and around the hotel, on foot, in cars and on bikes. We felt very safe even at night in the parking garage. The casino was not too smoky. Check in went smoothly. The girl that checked us in, Nicole, was very friendly and helpful and saw that we had a non smoking room on a high floor, facing the hills, just like we requested. We checked in about 1pm and even though check in is not until 3pm they had no problem letting us check in two hours early. The room was VERY comfortable. We had a king size bed that was very firm but plush and the sheets were great. The pillows were very comfortable. There was triple sheeting on the bed. The blackout curtains worked very well and kept the room absolutely dark, great the next morning after a late night when we wanted to sleep in. We didn't hear a sound from outside the room, not once while we were there. Air conditioning worked great and was very quiet. The hotel supplied soap, shampoo and shower gel from Bath and Body Works and the wife just loved that. We even had a bottle of mouthwash!The lighting was good in the room and so was the water pressure. Wireless internet worked great from the room when we purchased it for one day. There is a huge safe that you can set your own code for. It held our 15 in and 17 inch widescreen laptops and my wife's large purse and there was still room left! There is an ironing board and iron in the room, and a couch and coffee table, as well as a small dining table with two chairs. It was like a mini suite. I see that some reviews mentioned power and water problems earlier this month, but apparently that has been fixed. Our water pressure was great the entire time, and our lights never flickered once. The 42 in plasma TV had a nice selection of channels, for Vegas, and we hooked up an S video to it one night and watched a movie using a laptop. The picture on the DVD was great too. We didn't visit the pool area this time, but could see it from our room and it looked very inviting. Next time we will visit it for sure. The buffet had a great selection for lunch and we had a buy one get one free coupon given to us at check in. It was a great value at $7.99. We ate dinner in the Coronado Cafe one night. Wife had the T bone special and I had the rack of ribs. Both meals were very good. The graveyard specials were good too, and very reasonable. We don't gamble much, we do more sight seeing while we are in Vegas, but we did play the slots a little one night, and they were pretty loose for us. We came home ahead. The waitress came by frequently asking if we wanted something to drink. Every employee we met on the casino floor was friendly to us, whether we were gambling at the time or just observing or looking around. We didn't meet any employees that were rude or unfriendly during our stay. We liked that the South Point is a little ways from the strip. It was quieter there and we felt it was a great value for the money spent. We look forward to going back later this year and staying again at The South Point.	
