Jul 15 2008 	Fantastic and brilliant stay. Great price.	We only noticed this hotel via this website and are very grateful that we did.Firstly let me point out that this hotel is on Las Vegas Blvd S, but it is actually just over 5 miles from the main strip itself. Therefore, unless you have a car it may be unsuitable for you. They do provide shuttles to the strip, but am not sure how frequently they run.The hotel itself is fantastic, especially for the price we paid. We paid £261.00 (about $522), through expedia, for a 7 night stay. I thought this great value for money. Check-In was very smooth and with no problems. We requested a pool view room on a high floor and that is what we got. Ample free parking is available as well as Valet.The rooms are very spacious and clean. The maid did a fantastic job every day. The A/C worked great and is quite, it was 105f – 110f outside and the room was comfortably cool with the A/C on. The rooms have 42” Flat Screen TV and I personally found the beds comfortable. The pool area was also very clean. The main pool is in good size and about 3.5 feet deep. There is also a Children’s pool and I think this was 1.5 feet deep. There is a large Jacuzzi towards the back. There are many sunbeds available. The sun does not shine in the pool area until after 9.00am onwards (in July), so it is good use the Jacuzzi at this time.The Casino is very similar to all other casinos in LV, except this was the only place where I saw minimum 1 dollar bet roulette tables. Staff in the Casino are also very polit. Many places to eat within the hotel, with two places staying open until 5.00am. This was our first time in Vegas and we really enjoyed it and also our stay at this hotel. The only thing that will prevent me from staying at this hotel is my desire for next time to stay on the main strip.	
Jul 8 2008 	Yes its off the strip! Great Place	Stayed 6/28 - 7/3. (HOT 101-111 degrees)Had a rental car.Arrived at the hotel a little before 11:00 and waited in line for a couple of minutes. Front Desk informed me that they are not checking anyone in yet and to come back in about an hour. No problem for us, we checked our bags with the Bell desk and headed out to In N Out Burger. Its a ritual for us being from NY/NJ, we are deprived.Came back to the hotel around 12:30, waited a couple of minutes in line then were given a nice room on the 21st floor.Room Review:Very clean &amp; large. Bed was comfortable but sheets were a little rough (no big deal). One improvement I recommended was larger bath towels.Restaurants:Coronado Cafe - okay dinner type food. Didn't care for the chinese food but I am comparing it to NYC Chinatown.Baja Miguel's - Not bad. Was better then some of the chain restaurants (Chevy's, On the Border).Big Sur Oyster Bar - Good. Crispy fried Calamari &amp; chunky New England Clam Chowder.Casino:We lost but that's why they call it gambling. The drink hostesses were great, always coming around/fast service + cold beer. Overall the casino was clean and not very smokey.Check-Out:Waited in line for a couple of minutes. The only issue I had was a $15 per day charge for a room refrigerator. This was dropped b/c it was required for medical/medicine. I checked on this before I checked in but was something missed by the front desk, no biggie!Tips:1. If you have a car and are heading to the strip use the I-15 entrance at the back of hotel. You can fly up the highway and get off at many spots along the strip. Time &amp; gas saver.2. They sell liquor in the gift store in the casino.3. Graveyard specials @ Coronado's from 12:00 - 6:00am. Several dishes are $3 - $5.Things I would change:1. $10 a day fee to use the gym2. $12 a day for internet access3. Some employees need to learn how to smile at the front desk.	
