May 27 2008 	Fantastic Hotel	South Point really is a fantastic place to stay.The hotel is only a few years old so everything still feels nice and new.The rooms are lovely...huge with nice comfy beds.The food is great value and really quite good considering the low prices.The bowling alley is huge and is very cheap compared to the ones in the UK.The cinema is a great added extra.I fell lucky with the pool,because when i booked, the pool was closed and not due to re-open until 23rd May(2 days after my departure) due to construction work.However,it re-opened early and my son was delighted.It is a lovely heated pool and never got nowhere near crowded during our stay.It was nice to be able to chill out without the crowds.Be warned-----the jacuzzi pool is like stepping into a hot bath---quite strange in the middle of the desert.I diidnt go to Las Vegas for the gambling,but the casino seemed nice and light and airy.....not one hint of tobacco smoke.The hotel shuttle runs to the Mandalay Bay,with the last return trip at 1.30am.If you miss the shuttle the taxi fare from the Mandalay is around $15.I really cannot find anything negative to say about this hotel.I highly recommend it.p.s the construction work was just about completed during our stay.	
