May 10 2008 	Large beautiful rooms	We stayed at South Point for only one night while travelling through Vegas. It was very convenient for us being south of the strip and just off the interstate. We didn't have any delay checking in but then we also got there about 11 pm. Our room had already been charged to our card and there was a record of that so we had absolutley no problem with registration. The room was just as we expected, only better. New, large, beautful. Lovely toiletries in the bathroom. Bath was separate from sink and toilet - very smart idea! It was very quiet - didn't hear a thing from any where and I am a very light sleeper. In this age of the internet, folks should not be surprised by what they do or do not find in the rooms. The hotel web site is very clear about what is included. We could have used a fridge but knew ahead of time there wasn't one so no complaints from me for the lack of one! We ordered up room service. It was fast, the food was very good (and we are picky eaters) and the staff person was very professional. I would comment that folks who are staying longer might want to request a room change if they get a room in the front on the first few floors. You don't have a view at all - you are behind the front wall of the hotel! It didn't matter for us - we found it funny. I can understand the complaints from folks about the casino and smoke and registration being all in one place. That would be my only negative about this hotel. If you can get passed that, you will have a lovely big new room in a beautiful hotel. Earlier in this same holiday we stayed for 4 days in another hotel in Vegas and toured around most of the big properties. The one thing that we really liked was the stunning beautful lobbies. If this hotel had bothered to do that, I would have rated it a 5.	
