Apr 24 2008 	Not what we expected	After reading such great reviews, I was disappointed. More staff is definitely needed at registration as we were made to wait 20-30 minutes to check in. For a hotel that is supposed to be so new, I wasn't impressed. The only redeeming feature to our room was the plasma TV. The blanket on our bed had a hole in it. The handle to the very cheaply made dresser was almost hanging off. Everything about the room (except for the TV) was disappointing. Our window kept making this odd rattling noise every once in a while likely caused by the wind. We decided to make the best of it that night but we did check out a day early. Dinner at Silverado Steak House was very good and very good value - we were both impressed by our meals and the wonderful attentive service in this restaurant. Not having a pool was also a factor something which we should have checked out beforehand. My suggestion is that you can do better on the strip if you do your research.	
